column5: OK guys...10 days left in this "ice season" ...I hear lake is open in the middle and chunks of ice keep braking off the shore line and floating East...anyone know if there are any launches (preferably on the West side) that are free of ice? Thanks.  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
No, but I know of an access with 14" of ice
hahaha Sinker brother...if you now tell me there are also whities there...I am game
There are whities, but not many, and its a loooong ways to get them lol   S.

Well then I think we should concentrate on the boat access...I have a feeling if we manage to do it there are lot of whities waiting for us....and with so few of them been caught this season...imagine the show ha ha ha....the ones I got last weekend were very fat too  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
IBP is still frozen, was there this morning.

That is the one I was hoping to clear first as it is the most convenient for me....oh well...hope this warm temps this week will help...not much time left until the 15-th though....  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
